            padding: 0;
        }
        .container {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            color: #0056b3;
        }
        .content {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .footer {
            margin-top: 30px;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            color: #777;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
       <div class="logo-container" style="text-align: center;">
            <a href="#">
                <img style="width: 70px;" id="logo"
                     src="https://tiptop-stag.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/staging/TipTopDriver.png"
                     width="70" alt="" />
            </a>
        </div>
    

        <p>Dear {{customer_name}},</p>

        <div class="content">
            <p>I hope you're doing well. I’m writing to apologize for the incorrect response you received earlier, which was intended for another customer.</p>

            <p>We’ve now received your actual complaint and are reviewing it. Here’s a message from our team:</p>

  <p>Message from Admin:  {{admin_message}}</p>
            {{!-- <blockquote>
                Message from Admin:<br>
                "{{admin_message}}"
            </blockquote> --}}

            <p>You’ll hear back from us shortly with a proper response.</p>

            <p>Thank you for your understanding, and we apologize for any confusion.</p>

            <p>Best regards,<br>
           TipTop Cabby</p>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <p>This is an automated message; please do not reply to this email. If you have any questions, contact our support team.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
